snippet.textDisplay: My wife got rear ended by a dump truck in our 2017 Raptor before it was even a week old. The only damage was half of the bed and a small amount of frame damage in the rear. I told them if they didn’t total it they were putting on a new frame, I would not accept a repaired frame on a 6 day old truck. They replaced the frame and literally rebuilt the truck and it has been as good as brand new ever since. I also got diminished value for the car fax hit that it will take or I would be angry. The long and the short of it is that it was A LOT of work and the repair bill was almost $30,000. A lot of that was labor but still this will be an expensive project and I absolutely wish you the best of luck. And for what it’s worth, our 2017 Raptor super crew is the most favorite vehicle that my wife has ever driven and the vehicle that she most likes out of any that we have ever owned. Good luck!
